					<head>Halakhah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85113223" rend="visible">
						<summary>A collection of responses by Solomon ibn Adret and others.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85113223">
							<locus from="1r" to="434v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Responses</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">שאלות ותשובות </title>
							<note>
								<p>The title is given on folio 1r, 15r, and on a flyleaf at the beginning of the volume.</p>
								<p>Folios 1v-14v contain an index (imperfect) of the responses belonging to different sections.</p>
								<p>Each section begins with a series of responses by Solomon ibn Adret, and ends with replies on similar subjects by Isaac Alfasi. There are many other rabbinic authorities quoted throughout.</p>
								<p>A marginal annotator compared the manuscript with Teshuvot ha-Rashba as printed in Venice 1546, and with other editions. Against a large number of responses the same annotator has written the word 'meḥudeshet' (i.e. not known to exist elsewhere).</p>
							</note>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/27494766">Adret, Solomon ben Abraham, 1235-1310</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/27494766">אדרת, שלמה בן אברהם אבן (רשב"א)</persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
