					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>434 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>267</height>
										<width>200</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>180</height>
										<width>125</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>434 folios (+ 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and 4 at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 10 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Lacunae after folio 10, 11, 13, 14, 227.</p>
									<p>Defective at the end.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2" ruledLines="32" writtenLines="32">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Hard-point ruling is visible.</p>
									<p>Hair-side and flesh-side of folios is distinguishable.</p>
									<p>Initial word in each section is given in larger characters.</p>
									<p>Some marginal notes and additions are present.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi (North-African) semi-cursive script of the latter part of the 14th century. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folio 434r, 434v and [ii recto] contain a consecutive fragment of <name type="person" role="author">Daṿid Kimḥi</name> Sefer ha-shorashim. Each page of the fragment is divided in to 2 columns, with 36 or 37 lines to a column. Written in French-Ashkenazi semi-cursive script, probably of the earlier part of the 14th century.</p>
						</additions>
